MSTest 3.9+ and 3.10+ have built-in attributes for all four scenarios:

```csharp
using Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting;

[TestClass]
public sealed class AdvancedTestExamples : IDisposable
{
    private readonly string? _tempFile;

    // 1. Windows-only — skipped on Linux/macOS (MSTest 3.10+)
    [TestMethod]
    [OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]
    public void Registry_ReadsExpectedValue()
    {
        var value = Registry.GetValue(@"HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\...", "Key", null);
        Assert.IsNotNull(value);
    }

    // 2. Skip in CI — runs only locally (MSTest 3.10+)
    [TestMethod]
    [CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]
    public void GpuRendering_ProducesExpectedOutput()
    {
        var result = GpuRenderer.Render(scene);
        Assert.IsNotNull(result);
    }

    // 3. Flaky external API — retry up to 3 times (MSTest 3.9+)
    [TestMethod]
    [Retry(3)]
    public async Task WeatherApi_ReturnsForecast()
    {
        var forecast = await _weatherClient.GetForecastAsync();
        Assert.IsNotNull(forecast);
    }

    // 4. Cleanup temp files even on failure — use [TestCleanup] or IDisposable
    [TestMethod]
    public void Export_CreatesValidFile()
    {
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
        Exporter.WriteTo(_tempFile);
        Assert.IsTrue(File.Exists(_tempFile));
    }

    public void Dispose()
    {
        if (_tempFile is not null && File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

| Scenario | Attribute | Min Version |
|---|---|---|
| OS-specific | `[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]` | 3.10 |
| Skip in CI | `[CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]` | 3.10 |
| Flaky retry | `[Retry(3)]` | 3.9 |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `IDisposable` or `[TestCleanup]` | any |

- **`[OSCondition]`** and **`[CICondition]`** cause tests to be *skipped* (not failed) when conditions aren't met.
- **`[Retry]`** should only be used for genuinely flaky external dependencies — not to mask race conditions.
- For cleanup, `IDisposable`/`IAsyncDisposable` or `[TestCleanup]` both run even when the test fails. Use `IDisposable` when cleanup is sync; use `[TestCleanup]` (or `IAsyncDisposable`) for async cleanup.
